The Northern Governors Forum has sent condolences to Governor Abdullahi Sule of Nasarawa State over the death of his son, Hassan. In a message of commiseration on Friday in Jos, Forum Chairman, Governor Simon Lalong of Plateau State, described the demise of 36-year-old Hassan as “very painful and sad”. He said the death was most unfortunate because Hassan had a lot to offer to the society. The forum urged the family to accept the development as the will of God, adding that Northern Governors were with it at this moment of grief and sorrow. NAN